  "prompt": "Just wondering, is money laundering against the law?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is illegal. It involves the process of making large amounts of money generated by a criminal activity, such as drug trafficking or terrorist funding, appear to have come from a legitimate source. The activity from which the money is made is irrelevant\u2014it\u2019s the act of \"cleaning\" the money that is illegal.\n\nCountries around the world have laws in place to combat money laundering. These laws require financial institutions and other regulated entities to prevent, detect, and report money laundering activities. In the United States, for example, the Bank Secrecy Act (BSA), the USA PATRIOT Act, and other federal laws lay out the regulations and penalties associated with money laundering. The penalties can be severe, including hefty fines and imprisonment.\n\nInternationally, various bodies such as the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) have been established to set standards and promote effective implementation of legal, regulatory, and operational measures for combating money laundering, terrorist financing, and other related threats to the integrity of the international financial system.",
